First tergite (
Fig. 37
) long, 2.2–2.6 times as long as broad behind, its margin laterally from scutum very narrow, together with further tergites polished. Tergites 2 and 3 transverse, third tergite either as long as or longer than second tergite (
Fig. 37
). Hypopygium pointed, ovipositor sheath shorter than to as long as hind tibia + basitarsus combined.

Male: Similar to the female. Body 4–4.5(–5) mm long. Antenna as long as body and with 37–38 antennomeres. Melanic form: metasoma black (cf. 
VIERECK 1913: 640
).
